article.headline: Middle Tennessee 61, Ark.-Little Rock 60
article.story: LITTLE ROCK (AP) -- Desmond Yates hit 7-of-9 of his shots from the field Saturday night as Middle Tennessee edged Arkansas-Little Rock 61-60 in a Sun Belt Conference matchup. Yates finished with 15 points as the top scorer for the Blue Raiders (9-10, 5-4 SBC). MTSU led 32-25 at the half, but allowed the Trojans (9-12, 4-6) to get close in the second half. De'Andre Eggins led UALR's scoring with 17 points, while Rashad Jones-Jennings got a double-double with 15 points and 13 rebounds. Terrance Akins, who scored 13 points for the Trojans, was 3-of-5 from 3-point range. Calvin O'Neil added 11 points for MTSU, and Theryn Hudson scored 10.
